{{Infobox language |name=North-Western Mari |nativename=Йөтнӫмӓл-кӓсвел маре йӹлмӹ ''Jůtnṳ̊mäl-käsvel mare jÿlmÿ'' |states=[[Russia]] |region=[[Kirov Oblast]] ([[Yaransky District|Yaransky]], [[Tuzhinsky District|Tuzhinsky]], [[Kiknursky District|Kiknursky]], [[Sanchursky District|Sanchursky]] districts), [[Nizhny Novgorod Oblast]] ([[Tonshayevsky District|Tonshayevsky]], [[Sharangsky District|Sharangsky]], [[Tonkinsky District|Tonkinsky]] districts), [[Mari El]] (north of [[Kilemarsky District|Kilemarsky]] and [[Medvedevsky District|Medvedevsky]] districts) |speakers=7,000 |date=2012 |ref= |familycolor=Uralic |fam2=[[Finno-Ugric languages|Finno-Ugric]] |fam3=[[Finno-Permic languages|Finno-Permic]] |fam4=[[Finno-Volgaic languages|Finno-Volgaic]] |fam5=[[Mari language|Mari]] |iso3= |glotto=yara1249 |glottorefname=North-Western Mari }}
'''North-Western Mari''' (''Маре йӹлмӹ'') is a [[Uralic languages|Uralic]] language closely related to [[Hill Mari language|Hill Mari]] and [[Meadow Mari language|Meadow Mari]]. North-Western Mari is spoken in [[Russia]] in the [[Yaransky District|Yaransky]], [[Tuzhinsky District|Tuzhinsky]], [[Kiknursky District|Kiknursky]], [[Sanchursky District|Sanchursky]] districts of [[Kirov Oblast]], [[Tonshayevsky District|Tonshayevsky]], [[Sharangsky District|Sharangsky]] and [[Tonkinsky District|Tonkinsky]] districts of [[Nizhny Novgorod Oblast]] and partly in [[Kilemarsky District|Kilemarsky]] and [[Medvedevsky District|Medvedevsky]] districts of [[Mari El]]. It is written using the North-Western Mari [[Cyrillic script]], but doesn't have an official status in any subjects of [[Russian Federation]].
North-Western Mari people have difficulties with both other literary languages<ref>Taagepera R. The Finno-Ugric Republics and the Russian State. New York, 1999. P. 223.</ref>. The first book in North-Western Mari dialect ''{{lang|chm|Маре букварь}}'' ({{transl|chm|Mare bukvar}}, North-Western Mari primer) was printed in [[1995]] and become the language as a [[Written language|written]] one.
